# Iteration 10: Master nodepool RPC timeout under latency

## Evidence
Reliability calibration artifact: `test_logs/reliability/20260520-084035`

Run id: `rel-20260520084038-r01`

Observed:
- `/api/login` succeeded through the nodepool latency proxy.
- First `/api/upload-task` returned HTTP 502 after 5000ms.
- Error body: `rpc error: code = DeadlineExceeded desc = context deadline exceeded`.

## Fix
Changed master nodepool RPC timeout from a hard-coded 5 seconds to `nodepoolCallTimeout()`, defaulting to 30 seconds and configurable via `MASTER_NODEPOOL_TIMEOUT_SEC`.

Added `services/master/cmd/server/main_test.go::TestNodepoolCallTimeoutFromEnv`.

